WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.060 --> 00:00:17.196
As the highest military commander of the Netherlands.
[AI] 作为荷兰最高军事指挥官。

2
00:00:17.220 --> 00:00:20.236
with troops stationed around the world.
[AI] 驻扎在世界各地的军队。

3
00:00:20.260 --> 00:00:22.980
I'm really honored to be here today.
[AI] 今天能来到这里我真的很荣幸。

4
00:00:24.420 --> 00:00:28.596
When I look around this TEDxAmsterdam venue.
[AI] 当我环顾TEDxAmsterdam会场时。

5
00:00:28.620 --> 00:00:31.780
I see a very special audience.
[AI] 我看到一个非常特别的观众。

6
00:00:32.780 --> 00:00:36.684
You are the reason why I said yes
[AI] 你就是我答应的原因

7
00:00:36.708 --> 00:00:39.428
to the invitation to come here today.
[AI] 感谢你今天来这里的邀请。

8
00:00:41.340 --> 00:00:46.300
When I look around. I see people who want to make a contribution.
[AI] 当我环顾四周。我看到有人想做出贡献。

9
00:00:47.140 --> 00:00:50.540
I see people who want to make a better world.
[AI] 我看到有人想创造一个更美好的世界。

10
00:00:51.860 --> 00:00:55.796
by doing groundbreaking scientific work.
[AI] 通过做开创性的科学工作。

11
00:00:55.820 --> 00:00:58.260
by creating impressive works of art.
[AI] 通过创作令人印象深刻的艺术作品。

12
00:00:59.420 --> 00:01:03.620
by writing critical articles or inspiring books.
[AI] 通过写评论文章或鼓舞人心的书。

13
00:01:04.660 --> 00:01:06.860
by starting up sustainable businesses.
[AI] 通过创办可持续发展的企业。

14
00:01:08.180 --> 00:01:12.556
And you all have chosen your own instruments
[AI] 你们都选择了自己的乐器

15
00:01:12.580 --> 00:01:15.900
to fulfill this mission of creating a better world.
[AI] 完成创造更美好世界的使命。

16
00:01:17.300 --> 00:01:20.500
Some chose the microscope as their instrument.
[AI] 有些人选择显微镜作为他们的仪器。

17
00:01:21.420 --> 00:01:23.840
Others chose dancing or painting.
[AI] 其他人选择跳舞或绘画。

18
00:01:24.731 --> 00:01:26.804
or making music like we just heard.
[AI] 或者像我们刚刚听到的那样做音乐。

19
00:01:27.660 --> 00:01:28.980
Some chose the pen.
[AI] 有些人选择了钢笔。

20
00:01:30.380 --> 00:01:33.380
Others work through the instrument of money.
[AI] 其他人通过货币工具工作。

21
00:01:34.860 --> 00:01:38.300
Ladies and gentlemen. I made a different choice.
[AI] 女士们，先生们。我做了一个不同的选择。

22
00:01:52.660 --> 00:01:53.860
Thanks.
[AI] 谢谢

23
00:01:57.500 --> 00:01:58.700
Ladies and gentlemen ...
[AI] 女士们，先生们。。。

24
00:02:00.940 --> 00:02:02.916
(Laughter)
[AI] （众笑）

25
00:02:02.940 --> 00:02:07.460
(Applause)
[AI] （掌声）

26
00:02:08.851 --> 00:02:10.914
I share your goals.
[AI] 我同意你的目标。

27
00:02:12.060 --> 00:02:15.460
I share the goals of the speakers you heard before.
[AI] 我与你以前听到的发言者的目标相同。

28
00:02:17.340 --> 00:02:22.299
I did not choose to take up the pen.
[AI] 我没有选择拿起那支笔。

29
00:02:23.380 --> 00:02:26.620
the brush. the camera.
[AI] 刷子。照相机。

30
00:02:27.380 --> 00:02:30.420
I chose this instrument.
[AI] 我选择了这种乐器。

31
00:02:31.260 --> 00:02:33.780
I chose the gun.
[AI] 我选择了枪。

32
00:02:34.860 --> 00:02:37.316
For you. and you heard already.
[AI] 为你。你已经听说了。

33
00:02:37.340 --> 00:02:43.100
being so close to this gun may make you feel uneasy.
[AI] 离这把枪这么近可能会让你感到不安。

34
00:02:44.300 --> 00:02:45.900
It may even feel scary.
[AI] 这甚至可能让人感到害怕。

35
00:02:46.860 --> 00:02:50.180
A real gun at a few feet's distance.
[AI] 几英尺远的真枪。

36
00:02:51.300 --> 00:02:55.860
Let us stop for a moment and feel this uneasiness.
[AI] 让我们停下来，感受一下这种不安。

37
00:02:56.460 --> 00:02:57.740
You could even hear it.
[AI] 你甚至可以听到。

38
00:02:59.180 --> 00:03:01.356
Let us cherish the fact
[AI] 让我们珍惜这个事实

39
00:03:01.380 --> 00:03:06.140
that probably most of you have never been close to a gun.
[AI] 也许你们中的大多数人从未接近过枪。

40
00:03:07.620 --> 00:03:11.860
It means the Netherlands is a peaceful country.
[AI] 这意味着荷兰是一个和平的国家。

41
00:03:12.500 --> 00:03:15.020
The Netherlands is not at war.
[AI] 荷兰没有处于战争状态。

42
00:03:15.940 --> 00:03:20.180
It means soldiers are not needed to patrol our streets.
[AI] 这意味着不需要士兵来巡逻我们的街道。

43
00:03:21.420 --> 00:03:24.780
Guns are not a part of our lives.
[AI] 枪不是我们生活的一部分。

44
00:03:26.340 --> 00:03:30.100
In many countries. it is a different story.
[AI] 在许多国家。这是一个不同的故事。

45
00:03:31.260 --> 00:03:35.756
In many countries. people are confronted with guns.
[AI] 在许多国家。人们面临着枪支。

46
00:03:35.780 --> 00:03:37.636
They are oppressed.
[AI] 他们受到压迫。

47
00:03:37.660 --> 00:03:38.940
They are intimidated --
[AI] 他们被吓坏了--

48
00:03:40.060 --> 00:03:41.260
by warlords.
[AI] 由军阀控制。

49
00:03:42.420 --> 00:03:43.620
by terrorists.
[AI] 恐怖分子。

50
00:03:44.580 --> 00:03:45.780
by criminals.
[AI] 犯罪分子。

51
00:03:46.740 --> 00:03:48.780
Weapons can do a lot of harm.
[AI] 武器会造成很大的伤害。

52
00:03:49.860 --> 00:03:52.100
They are the cause of much distress.
[AI] 他们是造成许多痛苦的原因。

53
00:03:52.900 --> 00:03:56.940
Why then am I standing before you with this weapon?
[AI] 那我为什么拿着这个武器站在你面前？

54
00:03:57.900 --> 00:04:01.860
Why did I choose the gun as my instrument?
[AI] 我为什么选择枪作为我的工具？

55
00:04:03.100 --> 00:04:05.220
Today I want to tell you why.
[AI] 今天我想告诉你为什么。

56
00:04:05.980 --> 00:04:07.556
Today I want to tell you
[AI] 今天我想告诉你

57
00:04:07.580 --> 00:04:10.540
why I chose the gun to create a better world.
[AI] 为什么我选择枪来创造一个更美好的世界。

58
00:04:11.500 --> 00:04:15.660
And I want to tell you how this gun can help.
[AI] 我想告诉你这把枪有什么用。

59
00:04:17.980 --> 00:04:21.860
My story starts in the city of Nijmegen
[AI] 我的故事从奈梅根市开始

60
00:04:23.340 --> 00:04:24.940
in the east of the Netherlands.
[AI] 在荷兰东部。

61
00:04:26.140 --> 00:04:28.180
the city where I was born.
[AI] 我出生的城市。

62
00:04:30.300 --> 00:04:34.140
My father was a hardworking baker.
[AI] 我父亲是一位勤奋的面包师。

63
00:04:36.620 --> 00:04:39.476
but when he had finished work in the bakery.
[AI] 但当他在面包店完成工作时。

64
00:04:39.500 --> 00:04:42.220
he often told me and my brother stories.
[AI] 他经常给我和我兄弟讲故事。

65
00:04:43.460 --> 00:04:45.076
And most of the time.
[AI] 大多数时候。

66
00:04:45.100 --> 00:04:48.300
he told me this story I'm going to share with you now.
[AI] 他告诉了我这个故事，我现在要和你们分享。

67
00:04:50.140 --> 00:04:51.796
The story of what happened
[AI] 发生的事情的故事

68
00:04:51.820 --> 00:04:56.156
when he was a conscripted soldier in the Dutch armed forces
[AI] 当他是荷兰武装部队的应征士兵时

69
00:04:56.180 --> 00:04:58.580
at the beginning of the Second World War.
[AI] 在第二次世界大战开始时。

70
00:04:59.980 --> 00:05:02.260
The Nazis invaded the Netherlands.
[AI] 纳粹入侵荷兰。

71
00:05:02.860 --> 00:05:04.780
Their grim plans were evident.
[AI] 他们冷酷的计划显而易见。

72
00:05:05.660 --> 00:05:08.940
They meant to rule by means of repression.
[AI] 他们打算用镇压的手段来统治。

73
00:05:10.180 --> 00:05:13.580
Diplomacy had failed to stop the Germans.
[AI] 外交手段未能阻止德国人。

74
00:05:14.500 --> 00:05:17.572
Only brute force remained.
[AI] 只剩下蛮力了。

75
00:05:18.180 --> 00:05:20.140
It was our last resort.
[AI] 这是我们最后的办法。

76
00:05:21.420 --> 00:05:24.540
My father was there to provide it.
[AI] 我父亲是来提供的。

77
00:05:25.860 --> 00:05:29.676
As the son of a farmer who knew how to hunt.
[AI] 作为一个懂得打猎的农民的儿子。

78
00:05:29.700 --> 00:05:31.940
my father was an excellent marksman.
[AI] 我父亲是一名出色的射手。

79
00:05:32.740 --> 00:05:35.380
When he aimed. he never missed.
[AI] 当他瞄准的时候。他从未错过。

80
00:05:36.620 --> 00:05:39.636
At this decisive moment in Dutch history
[AI] 在荷兰历史上的这一决定性时刻

81
00:05:39.660 --> 00:05:44.476
my father was positioned on the bank of the river Waal
[AI] 我父亲被安置在瓦尔河畔

82
00:05:44.500 --> 00:05:46.100
near the city of Nijmegen.
[AI] 在奈梅根市附近。

83
00:05:47.500 --> 00:05:52.780
He had a clear shot at the German soldiers who came to occupy a free country.
[AI] 他向前来占领一个自由国家的德国士兵开了一枪。

84
00:05:53.740 --> 00:05:55.316
his country.
[AI] 他的国家。

85
00:05:55.340 --> 00:05:56.540
our country.
[AI] 我们的国家。

86
00:05:57.380 --> 00:05:59.780
He fired. Nothing happened.
[AI] 他开枪了。什么也没发生。

87
00:06:00.540 --> 00:06:01.726
He fired again.
[AI] 他又开枪了。

88
00:06:02.300 --> 00:06:04.860
No German soldier fell to the ground.
[AI] 没有德国士兵倒在地上。

89
00:06:05.980 --> 00:06:10.796
My father had been given an old gun
[AI] 我父亲得到了一把旧枪

90
00:06:10.820 --> 00:06:14.300
that could not even reach the opposite riverbank.
[AI] 甚至无法到达对面的河岸。

91
00:06:16.020 --> 00:06:18.796
Hitler's troops marched on.
[AI] 希特勒的军队继续前进。

92
00:06:18.820 --> 00:06:21.740
and there was nothing my father could do about it.
[AI] 我父亲对此无能为力。

93
00:06:23.220 --> 00:06:26.156
Until the day my father died.
[AI] 直到我父亲去世的那天。

94
00:06:26.180 --> 00:06:29.540
he was frustrated about missing these shots.
[AI] 他对错过这些镜头感到沮丧。

95
00:06:30.900 --> 00:06:32.460
He could have done something.
[AI] 他本可以做点什么的。

96
00:06:33.420 --> 00:06:35.236
But with an old gun.
[AI] 但是用一把旧枪。

97
00:06:35.260 --> 00:06:38.156
not even the best marksman in the armed forces
[AI] 甚至不是军队中最好的射手

98
00:06:38.180 --> 00:06:39.460
could have hit the mark.
[AI] 可能已经击中目标了。

99
00:06:40.940 --> 00:06:43.500
So this story stayed with me.
[AI] 所以这个故事一直伴随着我。

100
00:06:45.020 --> 00:06:46.396
Then in high school.
[AI] 然后在高中。

101
00:06:46.420 --> 00:06:49.980
I was gripped by the stories of the Allied soldiers --
[AI] 我被盟军士兵的故事吸引住了--

102
00:06:51.260 --> 00:06:56.516
soldiers who left the safety of their own homes and risked their lives
[AI] 离开自己安全的家园，冒着生命危险的士兵

103
00:06:56.540 --> 00:07:02.020
to liberate a country and a people that they didn't know.
[AI] 解放一个他们不认识的国家和人民。

104
00:07:02.820 --> 00:07:05.020
They liberated my birth town.
[AI] 他们解放了我的出生地。

105
00:07:06.460 --> 00:07:11.140
It was then that I decided I would take up the gun --
[AI] 就在那时，我决定拿起枪--

106
00:07:12.340 --> 00:07:16.996
out of respect and gratitude for those men and women
[AI] 出于对那些男人和女人的尊重和感激

107
00:07:17.020 --> 00:07:19.380
who came to liberate us.
[AI] 来解放我们的人。

108
00:07:20.820 --> 00:07:24.620
From the awareness that sometimes only the gun
[AI] 从意识到有时只有枪

109
00:07:25.660 --> 00:07:29.780
can stand between good and evil.
[AI] 能站在善与恶之间。

110
00:07:30.700 --> 00:07:34.716
And that is why I took up the gun --
[AI] 这就是我拿起枪的原因--

111
00:07:34.740 --> 00:07:35.940
not to shoot.
[AI] 不要开枪。

112
00:07:36.660 --> 00:07:38.116
not to kill.
[AI] 不要杀人。

113
00:07:38.140 --> 00:07:39.460
not to destroy.
[AI] 不要破坏。

114
00:07:40.420 --> 00:07:42.980
but to stop those who would do evil.
[AI] 而是阻止那些作恶的人。

115
00:07:44.180 --> 00:07:45.940
to protect the vulnerable.
[AI] 保护弱势群体。

116
00:07:47.100 --> 00:07:49.420
to defend democratic values.
[AI] 捍卫民主价值观。

117
00:07:50.500 --> 00:07:56.060
to stand up for the freedom we have to talk here today in Amsterdam
[AI] 为了捍卫自由，我们今天必须在阿姆斯特丹这里讲话

118
00:07:56.980 --> 00:07:59.300
about how we can make the world a better place.
[AI] 关于我们如何让世界变得更美好。

119
00:08:01.460 --> 00:08:02.676
Ladies and gentlemen.
[AI] 女士们，先生们。

120
00:08:02.700 --> 00:08:07.380
I do not stand here today to tell you about the glory of weapons.
[AI] 我今天站在这里不是要告诉你们武器的荣耀。

121
00:08:09.020 --> 00:08:11.020
I do not like guns.
[AI] 我不喜欢枪。

122
00:08:12.300 --> 00:08:15.780
And once you have been under fire yourself.
[AI] 一旦你自己受到攻击。

123
00:08:16.900 --> 00:08:19.436
it brings home even more clearly
[AI] 它更清楚地说明了这一点

124
00:08:19.460 --> 00:08:23.940
that a gun is not some macho instrument to brag about.
[AI] 枪不是吹嘘的大男子主义工具。

125
00:08:25.420 --> 00:08:26.916
I stand here today
[AI] 我今天站在这里

126
00:08:26.940 --> 00:08:32.300
to tell you about the use of the gun as an instrument of peace and stability.
[AI] 告诉你枪支作为和平与稳定的工具的用途。

127
00:08:34.940 --> 00:08:39.276
The gun may be one of the most important instruments of peace and stability
[AI] 枪支可能是和平与稳定的最重要工具之一

128
00:08:39.300 --> 00:08:40.780
that we have in this world.
[AI] 我们在这个世界上所拥有的。

129
00:08:41.820 --> 00:08:44.780
Now this may sound contradictory to you.
[AI] 这听起来可能与你的想法相矛盾。

130
00:08:46.220 --> 00:08:49.955
But not only have I seen with my own eyes
[AI] 但我不仅亲眼看到了

131
00:08:49.979 --> 00:08:53.002
during my deployments in Lebanon. Sarajevo
[AI] 在我在黎巴嫩的部署期间。萨拉热窝

132
00:08:53.026 --> 00:08:56.836
and as the Netherlands' Chief of Defence.
[AI] 作为荷兰的国防部长。

133
00:08:56.860 --> 00:09:02.780
this is also supported by cold. hard statistics.
[AI] 冷空气也支持这一点。硬统计。

134
00:09:03.780 --> 00:09:08.780
Violence has declined dramatically over the last 500 years.
[AI] 在过去500年中，暴力急剧减少。

135
00:09:09.860 --> 00:09:13.260
Despite the pictures we are shown daily in the news.
[AI] 尽管我们每天都在新闻中看到这些图片。

136
00:09:14.260 --> 00:09:19.076
wars between developed countries are no longer commonplace.
[AI] 发达国家之间的战争已不再司空见惯。

137
00:09:19.100 --> 00:09:20.356
The murder rate in Europe
[AI] 欧洲的谋杀率

138
00:09:20.380 --> 00:09:24.660
has dropped by a factor of 30 since the Middle Ages.
[AI] 自中世纪以来下降了30倍。

139
00:09:25.340 --> 00:09:28.116
And occurrences of civil war and repression
[AI] 以及内战和镇压事件

140
00:09:28.140 --> 00:09:30.940
have declined since the end of the Cold War.
[AI] 自冷战结束以来，这一数字一直在下降。

141
00:09:32.020 --> 00:09:37.340
Statistics show that we are living in a relatively peaceful era.
[AI] 统计数字表明，我们生活在一个相对和平的时代。

142
00:09:38.300 --> 00:09:39.450
Why?
[AI] 为什么？

143
00:09:39.860 --> 00:09:42.180
Why has violence decreased?
[AI] 为什么暴力有所减少？

144
00:09:43.100 --> 00:09:45.076
Has the human mind changed?
[AI] 人类的思想改变了吗？

145
00:09:45.100 --> 00:09:47.747
Well. we were talking about the human mind this morning.
[AI] 好今天早上我们在谈论人类的思维。

146
00:09:48.260 --> 00:09:53.076
Did we simply lose our beastly impulses for revenge.
[AI] 我们只是失去了复仇的兽性冲动。

147
00:09:53.100 --> 00:09:55.356
for violent rituals.
[AI] 用于暴力仪式。

148
00:09:55.380 --> 00:09:56.660
for pure rage?
[AI] 为了纯粹的愤怒？

149
00:09:58.180 --> 00:09:59.660
Or is there something else?
[AI] 还是有别的事？

150
00:10:01.460 --> 00:10:05.076
In his latest book. Harvard professor Steven Pinker --
[AI] 在他的新书中。哈佛大学教授史蒂文·平克--

151
00:10:05.100 --> 00:10:07.476
and many other thinkers before him --
[AI] 以及他之前的许多其他思想家--

152
00:10:07.500 --> 00:10:12.316
concludes that one of the main drivers
[AI] 得出结论，主要驱动因素之一

153
00:10:12.340 --> 00:10:14.876
behind less violent societies
[AI] 在不那么暴力的社会背后

154
00:10:14.900 --> 00:10:17.780
is the spread of the constitutional state
[AI] 是宪政国家的传播吗

155
00:10:18.900 --> 00:10:22.084
and the introduction. on a large scale.
[AI] 以及导言。大规模地。

156
00:10:22.108 --> 00:10:25.780
of the state monopoly on the legitimized use of violence --
[AI] 国家对合法使用暴力的垄断--

157
00:10:27.260 --> 00:10:31.780
legitimized by a democratically elected government.
[AI] 被民选政府合法化。

158
00:10:32.940 --> 00:10:38.420
legitimized by checks and balances and an independent judicial system.
[AI] 通过制衡和独立的司法制度使其合法化。

159
00:10:39.460 --> 00:10:42.516
In other words. a state monopoly
[AI] 换句话说。国家垄断

160
00:10:42.540 --> 00:10:47.020
that has the use of violence well under control.
[AI] 这使得暴力的使用得到了很好的控制。

161
00:10:48.220 --> 00:10:54.420
Such a state monopoly on violence. first of all. serves as a reassurance.
[AI] 这样的国家垄断了暴力。首先这是一种安慰。

162
00:10:55.980 --> 00:10:58.796
It removes the incentive for an arms race
[AI] 它消除了军备竞赛的动机

163
00:10:58.820 --> 00:11:02.260
between potentially hostile groups in our societies.
[AI] 在我们社会中潜在的敌对团体之间。

164
00:11:03.340 --> 00:11:06.116
Secondly. the presence of penalties
[AI] 其次惩罚的存在

165
00:11:06.140 --> 00:11:09.796
that outweigh the benefits of using violence
[AI] 这超过了使用暴力的好处

166
00:11:09.820 --> 00:11:11.940
tips the balance even further.
[AI] 这进一步打破了平衡。

167
00:11:13.140 --> 00:11:14.956
Abstaining from violence
[AI] 戒除暴力

168
00:11:14.980 --> 00:11:18.100
becomes more profitable than starting a war.
[AI] 比发动战争更有利可图。

169
00:11:19.420 --> 00:11:24.020
Now nonviolence starts to work like a flywheel.
[AI] 现在，非暴力开始像飞轮一样运转。

170
00:11:24.980 --> 00:11:27.220
It enhances peace even further.
[AI] 它进一步促进了和平。

171
00:11:28.660 --> 00:11:31.660
Where there is no conflict. trade flourishes.
[AI] 没有冲突的地方。贸易繁荣。

172
00:11:33.300 --> 00:11:37.260
And trade is another important incentive against violence.
[AI] 而贸易是反对暴力的另一个重要诱因。

173
00:11:38.340 --> 00:11:44.140
With trade. there's mutual interdependency and mutual gain between parties.
[AI] 与贸易有关。各方之间存在着相互依赖和互利。

174
00:11:45.220 --> 00:11:50.276
And when there is mutual gain. both sides stand to lose more
[AI] 当双方都有利益的时候。双方都会损失更多

175
00:11:50.300 --> 00:11:53.133
than they would gain if they started a war.
[AI] 如果他们发动战争，他们会得到更多。

176
00:11:54.700 --> 00:11:59.156
War is simply no longer the best option.
[AI] 战争不再是最好的选择。

177
00:11:59.180 --> 00:12:02.754
and that is why violence has decreased.
[AI] 这就是暴力减少的原因。

178
00:12:04.900 --> 00:12:06.676
This. ladies and gentlemen.
[AI] 这女士们，先生们。

179
00:12:06.700 --> 00:12:11.540
is the rationale behind the existence of my armed forces.
[AI] 是我的军队存在的理由。

180
00:12:12.380 --> 00:12:16.780
The armed forces implement the state monopoly on violence.
[AI] 武装部队对暴力实行国家垄断。

181
00:12:17.460 --> 00:12:19.916
We do this in a legitimized way
[AI] 我们这样做是合法的

182
00:12:19.940 --> 00:12:25.780
only after our democracy has asked us to do so.
[AI] 只有在我们的民主要求我们这样做之后。

183
00:12:26.900 --> 00:12:32.076
It is this legitimate. controlled use of the gun
[AI] 这是合法的。枪支的控制使用

184
00:12:32.100 --> 00:12:33.916
that has contributed greatly
[AI] 这作出了巨大贡献

185
00:12:33.940 --> 00:12:39.500
to reducing the statistics of war. conflict and violence around the globe.
[AI] 减少战争的统计数字。全球的冲突和暴力。

186
00:12:40.340 --> 00:12:43.876
It is this participation in peacekeeping missions
[AI] 正是这种对维和特派团的参与

187
00:12:43.900 --> 00:12:47.780
that has led to the resolution of many civil wars.
[AI] 这导致了许多内战的解决。

188
00:12:48.580 --> 00:12:53.860
My soldiers use the gun as an instrument of peace.
[AI] 我的士兵们把枪当作和平的工具。

189
00:12:55.100 --> 00:12:59.220
And this is exactly why failed states are so dangerous.
[AI] 这正是失败国家如此危险的原因。

190
00:13:00.460 --> 00:13:05.260
Failed states have no legitimized. democratically controlled use of force.
[AI] 失败的国家没有合法性。民主控制的武力使用。

191
00:13:06.060 --> 00:13:11.671
Failed states do not know of the gun as an instrument of peace and stability.
[AI] 失败的国家不知道枪支是和平与稳定的工具。

192
00:13:13.420 --> 00:13:19.780
That is why failed states can drag down a whole region into chaos and conflict.
[AI] 这就是为什么失败的国家可以把整个地区拖入混乱和冲突。

193
00:13:20.780 --> 00:13:24.676
That is why spreading the concept of the constitutional state
[AI] 这就是为什么要传播宪政国家的概念

194
00:13:24.700 --> 00:13:28.260
is such an important aspect of our foreign missions.
[AI] 这是我们外交任务的一个重要方面。

195
00:13:29.340 --> 00:13:33.076
That is why we are trying to build a judicial system
[AI] 这就是为什么我们正在努力建立一个司法系统

196
00:13:33.100 --> 00:13:35.140
right now in Afghanistan.
[AI] 现在在阿富汗。

197
00:13:36.380 --> 00:13:40.636
That is why we train police officers. we train judges.
[AI] 这就是我们培训警官的原因。我们培训法官。

198
00:13:40.660 --> 00:13:43.420
we train public prosecutors around the world.
[AI] 我们在世界各地培训检察官。

199
00:13:44.420 --> 00:13:45.756
And that is why --
[AI] 这就是为什么--

200
00:13:45.780 --> 00:13:49.076
and in the Netherlands. we are very unique in that --
[AI] 在荷兰。我们在这方面非常独特--

201
00:13:49.100 --> 00:13:52.836
that is why the Dutch constitution states
[AI] 这就是荷兰宪法规定的原因

202
00:13:52.860 --> 00:13:56.116
that one of the main tasks of the armed forces
[AI] 这是军队的主要任务之一

203
00:13:56.140 --> 00:14:00.340
is to uphold and promote the international rule of law.
[AI] 就是要维护和促进国际法治。

204
00:14:02.940 --> 00:14:04.516
Ladies and gentlemen.
[AI] 女士们，先生们。

205
00:14:04.540 --> 00:14:10.603
looking at this gun. we are confronted with the ugly side of the human mind.
[AI] 看看这把枪。我们面临着人类思想丑陋的一面。

206
00:14:12.460 --> 00:14:18.476
Every day I hope that politicians. diplomats. development workers
[AI] 我每天都希望政治家们。外交官。发展工作者

207
00:14:18.500 --> 00:14:21.956
can turn conflict into peace
[AI] 可以把冲突变成和平

208
00:14:21.980 --> 00:14:23.996
and threat
[AI] 和威胁

209
00:14:24.020 --> 00:14:25.242
into hope.
[AI] 进入希望。

210
00:14:25.860 --> 00:14:30.636
And I hope that one day armies can be disbanded
[AI] 我希望有一天军队可以解散

211
00:14:30.660 --> 00:14:33.556
and humans will find a way of living together
[AI] 人类将找到一种共同生活的方式

212
00:14:33.580 --> 00:14:35.637
without violence and oppression.
[AI] 没有暴力和压迫。

213
00:14:37.020 --> 00:14:39.620
But until that day comes.
[AI] 但在那一天到来之前。

214
00:14:40.700 --> 00:14:46.076
we will have to make ideals and human failure
[AI] 我们必须使理想和人类失败

215
00:14:46.100 --> 00:14:47.780
meet somewhere in the middle.
[AI] 在中间相遇。

216
00:14:48.740 --> 00:14:53.756
Until that day comes. I stand for my father
[AI] 直到那一天到来。我代表我父亲

217
00:14:53.780 --> 00:14:57.220
who tried to shoot the Nazis with an old gun.
[AI] 他试图用一把旧枪射杀纳粹。

218
00:14:58.020 --> 00:15:04.076
I stand for my men and women who are prepared to risk their lives
[AI] 我支持那些准备冒生命危险的人

219
00:15:04.100 --> 00:15:07.020
for a less violent world for all of us.
[AI] 为我们所有人创造一个不那么暴力的世界。

220
00:15:08.820 --> 00:15:14.716
I stand for this soldier who suffered partial hearing loss
[AI] 我代表这个部分失聪的士兵

221
00:15:14.740 --> 00:15:17.876
and sustained permanent injuries to her leg.
[AI] 她的腿受了永久伤。

222
00:15:17.900 --> 00:15:22.050
when she was hit by a rocket on a mission in Afghanistan.
[AI] 当她在阿富汗执行任务时被火箭击中。

223
00:15:24.420 --> 00:15:26.196
Ladies and gentlemen.
[AI] 女士们，先生们。

224
00:15:26.220 --> 00:15:31.476
until the day comes when we can do away with the gun.
[AI] 直到有一天我们可以扔掉枪。

225
00:15:31.500 --> 00:15:34.356
I hope we all agree
[AI] 我希望大家都同意

226
00:15:34.380 --> 00:15:38.340
that peace and stability do not come free of charge.
[AI] 和平与稳定不是免费的。

227
00:15:39.660 --> 00:15:44.380
It takes hard work. often behind the scenes.
[AI] 这需要艰苦的工作。通常在幕后。

228
00:15:45.460 --> 00:15:50.140
It takes good equipment and well-trained. dedicated soldiers.
[AI] 它需要良好的设备和训练有素的员工。忠诚的士兵。

229
00:15:51.100 --> 00:15:56.036
I hope you will support the efforts of our armed forces
[AI] 我希望你们支持我们军队的努力

230
00:15:56.060 --> 00:15:59.076
to train soldiers like this young captain
[AI] 训练像这位年轻的上尉这样的士兵

231
00:15:59.100 --> 00:16:01.996
and provide her with a good gun.
[AI] 给她一把好枪。

232
00:16:02.020 --> 00:16:04.780
instead of the bad gun my father was given.
[AI] 给我父亲的不是那把坏枪。

233
00:16:05.620 --> 00:16:10.300
I hope you will support our soldiers when they are out there.
[AI] 我希望当我们的士兵在那里的时候，你们会支持他们。

234
00:16:11.340 --> 00:16:12.580
when they come home
[AI] 当他们回家的时候

235
00:16:13.820 --> 00:16:16.820
and when they are injured and need our care.
[AI] 当他们受伤需要我们照顾的时候。

236
00:16:17.660 --> 00:16:22.476
They put their lives on the line. for us. for you.
[AI] 他们冒着生命危险。对我们来说。为你。

237
00:16:22.500 --> 00:16:25.460
and we cannot let them down.
[AI] 我们不能让他们失望。

238
00:16:26.460 --> 00:16:30.796
I hope you will respect my soldiers.
[AI] 我希望你们尊重我的士兵。

239
00:16:30.820 --> 00:16:32.780
this soldier with this gun.
[AI] 这个拿着枪的士兵。

240
00:16:33.740 --> 00:16:36.482
Because she wants a better world.
[AI] 因为她想要一个更美好的世界。

241
00:16:37.060 --> 00:16:41.180
Because she makes an active contribution to a better world.
[AI] 因为她对一个更美好的世界做出了积极的贡献。

242
00:16:41.900 --> 00:16:44.780
just like all of us here today.
[AI] 就像今天在座的所有人一样。

243
00:16:45.700 --> 00:16:47.156
Thank you very much.
[AI] 非常感谢你。

244
00:16:47.180 --> 00:16:52.540
(Applause)
[AI] （掌声）